{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, a hospital stay with this DRG code may truly contain MCC, but the MCC would not be labeled as positive in the training set.",
    "To address this challenge, we formulated rules in both the DRGs dissection phase (extracting base DRGs and CC/MCC from DRGs) and the inference phase (deriving DRGs based on base DRGs and CC/MCC).",
    "These rules cater to various split scenarios, thus improving accuracy.",
    "Implementing such rules has culminated in a final DRG prediction accuracy close to single-label prediction (51.5% vs. 52.0%).",
    "Our error analysis also revealed intriguing observations."
  ]
}